    "body": "Thanks! I've been struggling with this and it works with the 2.10 files (https://raw.githubusercontent.com/ipython/ipython-components/2.1.0/codemirror/keymap/emacs.js).\n\nIt looks like they changed the way that CodeMirror loads modules, the new version has this at the top:\n\n```\n(function(mod) {\n  if (typeof exports == \"object\" && typeof module == \"object\") // CommonJS\n    mod(require(\"../lib/codemirror\"));\n  else if (typeof define == \"function\" && define.amd) // AMD\n    define([\"../lib/codemirror\"], mod);\n  else // Plain browser env\n    mod(CodeMirror);\n})(function(CodeMirror) {\n```\n\nI think now CodeMirror needs to be informed of which modules to load instead of using require to load manually. However, I'm not familiar enough with this and this workaround seems to work for now.\n"
  },
