    "body": "Note for ipython 4.0, custom.js is in $HOME/.jupyter/custom and the following lines work:\n\n```\nfunction to(mode) {\n    var mode = mode || 'vim'\n    function to_mode(c) { return c.code_mirror.setOption('keyMap', mode);};\n    IPython.notebook.get_cells().map(to_mode);\n    IPython.Cell.options_default.cm_config.keyMap = mode;\n}\nrequire([\"base/js/namespace\", \"base/js/events\"], function (IPython, events) {\n    events.on(\"notebook_loaded.Notebook\", function () {\n        require([\"components/codemirror/keymap/emacs\"], function () { \n            to('emacs')\n            console.log('emacs.js loaded')\n        });\n    });\n});\n```\n\nI don't understand why but waiting on app_initialized.NotebookApp doesn't seem to work in Jupyter/Ipython 4.0.   notebook_loaded.Notebook does work.\n\nLooks like this should now be a Jupyter notebook issue.  \n"
  },
