    "body": "@nrhine1 This doesn't work for me. If you wanted to set this option, you would have to do it like so:\n\n``` javascript\nrequire([\n    'base/js/namespace',\n    'base/js/events',\n], function (IPython, events) {\n\n    function to(mode) {\n        // Note: This doesn't work because 'mode' is a string\n        // mode.setOption(\"extraKeys\", {\"Ctrl-v\": false});\n        function to_mode(c) { \n            c.code_mirror.setOption('keyMap', mode);\n            c.code_mirror.getOption('extraKeys')[\"Ctrl-V\"] = false;  // added\n        };\n        IPython.notebook.get_cells().map(to_mode);\n        require(\"notebook/js/cell\").Cell.options_default.cm_config.keyMap = mode;\n        require(\"notebook/js/cell\").Cell.options_default.cm_config.extraKeys[\"Ctrl-V\"] = false;  // added\n    };\n\n    events.on('notebook_loaded.Notebook', function () {\n        require([\"codemirror/keymap/emacs\"], function () {\n            to('emacs')\n            console.log('emacs.js loaded')\n        });\n    });\n});\n```\n\nNote the two lines with the `// added` comment. However, this doesn't work for me; I still get the cursor movement behavior. It may have appeared to work for you because your snippet raises an error, which disables the Emacs keybindings entirely.\n\nI tried a bunch of things (changing `extraKeys`, `customKeys`, etc) but nothing that I could do would restore the default `Ctrl-V` pasting behavior. I think it's just not possible with CodeMirror at the moment! Also, loading `.emacs` files definitely is not possible with CodeMirror, and likely never will be; the architectures are entirely different.\n\n---\n\nOne annoyance I was having is that `Ctrl-Shift--`, which I use as undo, is mapped by Jupyter as \"Split cell at cursor\". I have modified my `jupyter.js` snippet to remove this shortcut (not sure if this is the right place for it, but it works.\n\n``` javascript\nrequire([\n    'base/js/namespace',\n    'base/js/events',\n], function (IPython, events) {\n\n    function to(mode) {\n        function to_mode(c) {\n            c.code_mirror.setOption('keyMap', mode);\n        };\n        IPython.notebook.get_cells().map(to_mode);\n        require(\"notebook/js/cell\").Cell.options_default.cm_config.keyMap = mode;\n    };\n\n    events.on('notebook_loaded.Notebook', function () {\n        require([\"codemirror/keymap/emacs\"], function () {\n            to('emacs');\n            console.log('emacs.js loaded');\n        });\n\n        // Also remove Ctrl-Shift-- as Emacs uses this for undo\n        IPython.keyboard_manager.edit_shortcuts.remove_shortcut('ctrl-shift--');\n        IPython.keyboard_manager.edit_shortcuts.remove_shortcut('ctrl-shift-subtract');\n    });\n});\n```\n\nNote the last three lines in the `event.on` function.\n"
