    "body": "@tbekolay you're right, it was because `emacs` mode failed to load at all. My wealth of JS experience seemed to have failed me... Thanks for trying it out and letting me know!\n\nHowever, I got it to work (both `emacs` mode and `Ctrl-V` copy from system buffer;) by using:\n\n``` javascript\nc.code_mirror.setOption('keyMap', mode);\nc.code_mirror.setOption('extraKeys', {\"Ctrl-V\" : false});  // added\n```\n\nso the total snippet becomes:\n\n``` javascript\nrequire([\n    'base/js/namespace',\n    'base/js/events',\n], function (IPython, events) {\n\n    function to(mode) {\n\n\n        function to_mode(c) { \n            c.code_mirror.setOption('keyMap', mode);\n            c.code_mirror.setOption('extraKeys', {\"Ctrl-V\" : false});  // added\n        };\n        IPython.notebook.get_cells().map(to_mode);  \n        require(\"notebook/js/cell\").Cell.options_default.cm_config.keyMap = mode;\n    };\n\n    events.on('notebook_loaded.Notebook', function () {\n        require([\"codemirror/keymap/emacs\"], function () {\n            to('emacs')\n            console.log('emacs.js loaded')\n        });\n    });\n});\n```\n\nHopefully this works for you too? I'm using ipython notebook version 3.2.1 on Ubuntu 14.04. \n"
